-- Example channel map for LiveCC's optional per-speaker routing.
--
-- To use: copy this file next to the installed `livecc` program on your CC
-- computer, rename it to `livecc.speakers`, and edit the names below to match
-- your own speakers (run `peripheral.getNames()` from the Lua prompt, or just
-- `livecc <url>` once with no map -- it lists whatever it finds).
--
-- Any attached speaker NOT listed here stays silent once a map is in use --
-- there's no automatic mono fallback, so list every speaker you want to hear.
--
-- Available roles: mono, front_left, front_right, center, lfe,
--                   surround_left, surround_right, rear_left, rear_right
-- (docs/cc-media-format.md section 4.6 has the full channel-role reference.)
--
-- This example wires up a stereo pair. Positional roles only produce sound
-- once the source audio actually has that many channels and the server
-- negotiates them -- otherwise the server falls back to mono.

{
    left = "front_left",
    right = "front_right",
}
